obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5065)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5065&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Regional Rural Banks`
  line `Act, 1976.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 26th day of September, 1975.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5066)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5066&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board", in relation to a Regional Rural Bank, means the Board of directors of that Regional`
  line `Rural Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairman", in relation to a Regional Rural Bank, means the individual appointed or`
  line `re-appointed under sub-section (1) of section 11 as the Chairman of that bank;`
  line
  line `(c) "director", in relation to a Regional Rural Bank, means a member of the Board of that bank;`
  line ^1
  line
  line `[(ca) "National Bank" means the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development`
  line `established under section 3 of the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development Act, 1981`
  line `(61 of 1981);]`
  line
  line `(d) "notified area" means the local limits, specified under sub-section (1) of section 3, within`
  line `which a Regional Rural Bank shall operate;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "Regional Rural Bank" means a Regional Rural Bank established under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(g) "Sponsor Bank", in relation to a Regional Rural Bank, means a bank by which such Regional`
  line `Rural Bank has been sponsored;`
  line
  line `(h) "State Government" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a Regional Rural Bank established in a Union territory, the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a Regional Rural Bank established in a State, the Government of that State;`
  line
  line `(i) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act;`
  line
  line `(j) words and expressions used herein and not defined either in this Act or in the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), but defined in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), shall have`
  line `the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5067)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Regional Rural Banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5067&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `if requested so to do by a Sponsor Bank, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish in a State or`
  line `Union territory, one or more Regional Rural Banks with such name as may be specified in the notification`
  line `and may, by the said or subsequent notification, specify the local limits within which each Regional Rural`
  line `Bank shall operate.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Regional Rural Bank shall be a body corporate with perpetual succession and a common`
  line `seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to`
  line `contract and may sue and be sued in its name.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) It shall be the duty of the Sponsor Bank to aid and assist the Regional Rural Bank, sponsored by`
  line `it, by--`
  line
  line `(a) subscribing to the share capital of such Regional Rural Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) training personnel of such Regional Rural Bank; and`
  line
  line `(c) providing such managerial and financial assistance to such Regional Rural Bank ^2`
  line `***, as may`
  line `be mutually agreed upon between the Sponsor Bank and the Regional Rural Bank:`
  line
  line 3
  line `* * * * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 3, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line
  line `2. The words "during the first five years of its functioning" omitted by Act 14 of 2015, s. 2 (w.e.f. 4-2-2016).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-2-12016).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5068)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Offices and agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 4, for "Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5068&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Regional Rural Bank shall have its head office at such place in the`
  line `notified area as the Central Government may, after consultation with the ^1`
  line `[National Bank] and the`
  line `Sponsor Bank, specify by notification in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) A Regional Rural Bank may, if it is of opinion that it is necessary so to do, establish its branches`
  line `or agencies at any place in the notified area.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5069)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Authorised capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5069&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The authorised capital of each Regional Rural Bank shall be ^1`
  line `[two thousand`
  line `crore of rupees, divided into two hundred crore of fully paid-up shares of ten rupees each]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the ^2`
  line `[National Bank] and the`
  line `Sponsor Bank, increase or reduce such authorised capital; so, however, that the authorised capital shall`
  line `not be reduced below ^3`
  line `[one crore of rupees, and the shares shall be, in all cases, fully paid-up shares of`
  line `ten rupees each].`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 14 of 2015, s. 3, for "five crores of rupees divided into five lakhs of fully paid-up shares of one hundred`
  line `rupees each" (w.e.f. 4-2-2016).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 5, for "Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 14 of 2015, s. 3, for "twenty-five lakhs of rupees, and the shares shall be, in all cases, fully paid-up shares of`
  line `one hundred rupees each" (w.e.f. 4-2-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5070)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Issued capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5070&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) The issued capital of each Regional Rural Bank shall, in the first instance,`
  line `be such as may be fixed by the Central Government in this behalf, but it shall in no case be less than ^2`
  line [one
  line ^2
  line `[one crore of rupees].]`
  line
  line `(2) Of the capital issued by a Regional Rural Bank under sub-section (1), fifty per cent. shall`
  line `be subscribed by the Central Government; fifteen per cent. by the concerned State Government and`
  line `thirty-five per cent. by the Sponsor Bank.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that in case the Regional Rural Bank raises its capital from sources other than the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government or the Sponsor Bank, the shareholding of the Central Government`
  line `and the Sponsor Bank shall not be less than fifty-one per cent.:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government shall consult the concerned State Government if the`
  line `level of shareholding in the Regional Rural Bank of such State Government is reduced below fifteen`
  line `per cent.]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(2A) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Sponsor Bank and the State`
  line `Government, by notification, either raise or reduce the limit of shareholding of the Central Government,`
  line `the State Government or the Sponsor Bank specified in sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall consult the concerned State Government before reducing`
  line `the limit of shareholding of such State Government.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may, after consultation with the ^5`
  line `[National Bank], the concerned State Government`
  line `and the Sponsor Bank and with the prior approval of the Central Government, from time to time, increase`
  line `the issued capital of the Regional Rural Bank; and, where additional capital is issued, such capital shall`
  line `also be subscribed in the same proportion as is specified in sub-section (2)`
  line ^4
  line `[or, as the case may be,`
  line `notified by the Central Government under sub-section (2A)].`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 6, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2015, s. 4, for "“twenty-five lakhs of rupees or exceed one crore of rupees" (w.e.f. 4-2-2016).`
  line
  line `. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-2-2016).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 2015, s. 4 (w.e.f. 4-2-2016).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 6, for "Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5071)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Shares to be approved securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5071&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Acts hereinafter`
  line `mentioned in this section, the shares of a Regional Rural Bank shall be deemed to be included among the`
  line `securities enumerated in section 20 of the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882), and shall also be deemed`
  line `to be approved securities for the purposes of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5072)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Management.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5072&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the general superintendence, direction`
  line `and management of the affairs and business of a Regional Rural Bank shall vest in a Board of directors`
  line `who may exercise all the powers and discharge all the functions which may be exercised or discharged by`
  line `the Regional Rural Bank.`
  line `(2) In discharging its functions, the Board shall act on business principles and shall have due regard to`
  line `public interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (5073)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Board of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5073&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of directors shall consist of the Chairman appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 11, and the following other members, namely:--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) two directors, who are not officers of the Central Government, State Government, Reserve`
  line `Bank, National Bank, Sponsor Bank or any other bank, to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided that no person shall be nominated as a director, if he is already a director on the Board`
  line `Board of any other Regional Rural Bank;]`
  line
  line `(b) one director, who is an officer of the Reserve Bank, to be nominated by that Bank;`
  line
  line `(c) one director, who is an officer of the National Bank, to be nominated by that Bank;`
  line
  line `(d) two directors, who are officers of the Sponsor Bank, to be nominated by that Bank; and`
  line
  line `(e) two directors, who are officers of the concerned State Government, to be nominated by that`
  line `Government:]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(f) such number of directors elected by the shareholders other than the directors nominated by`
  line `the Central Government, the State Government, the Sponsor Bank and other institutions owned or`
  line `controlled by the Central Government or the State Government, whose names are entered in the`
  line `register of shareholders of the Regional Rural Bank at least ninety days before the date of the meeting`
  line `in which the election of directors takes place on the following basis, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) where the total amount of equity share capital issued to such shareholders is ten per cent.`
  line `or less of the total issued equity capital, one director shall be elected from such shareholders;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the total amount of equity share capital issued to such shareholders is more than ten`
  line `per cent. but less than twenty-five per cent. of the total issued equity capital, two directors shall`
  line `be elected from the shareholders including the shareholders referred to in sub-clause (i);`
  line
  line `(iii) where the total amount of equity share capital issued to such shareholders is twenty-five`
  line `per cent. or more of the total issued equity capital, three directors shall be elected from the`
  line `shareholders including shareholders referred to in sub-clauses (i) and (ii).]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may increase the number of members of the Board; so, however, that`
  line `the number of directors does not exceed fifteen in the aggregate and also prescribe the manner in which`
  line `the additional number may be filled in.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(3) The Central Government may appoint an officer of the Central Government on the Board of`
  line `Regional Rural Banks, if it considers necessary for the purposes of effective functioning of the Regional`
  line `Rural Banks.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for clauses (a), (b) and (c) (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 14 of 2015, s. 5 (w.e.f. 4-2-2016).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 14 of 2015, s. 5 (w.e.f. 4-2-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (5074)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Term of office of director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for section 10 (w.e.f. 4-2-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5074&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[10. Term of office of director.--A director nominated under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 9 shall hold office during the pleasure of the Central Government and for such term, not`
  line `exceeding three years, from the date on which he assumes his office, as the Central Government may`
  line `specify at the time of his nomination and shall be eligible for renomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such director shall hold office either continuously or intermittently for a period`
  line `exceeding six years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5075)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Chairman.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5075&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1`
  line `[The Sponsor Bank] shall appoint an individual to be the Chairman of a`
  line `Regional Rural Bank and specify the period, not exceeding five years, for which such individual shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), hold office as the Chairman:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided that no appointment of such an individual shall be made,--`
  line
  line `(a) if such an individual is an officer of the Sponsor Bank, except after consultation with the`
  line `National Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, except with the prior approval of the Central Government.]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) the Sponsor Bank shall have the right to terminate the term of office of the Chairman at any`
  line `time before the expiry of the period specified in sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that no such termination shall be made,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the Chairman is an officer of the Sponsor Bank, except after consultation with the`
  line `National Bank; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, except with the prior approval of the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the Chairman is not an officer of the Central Government, State`
  line `Government, Reserve Bank, National Bank, Sponsor Bank or any other bank, he shall be given notice`
  line `of not less than three months in writing or three months' salary and allowances in lieu of such notice;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the Chairman shall have the right to resign his office at any time before the expiry of the`
  line `period specified in sub-section (1) by giving to the Sponsor Bank, notice of not less than three months`
  line `in writing.]`
  line
  line `(2) The individual, appointed as a Chairman under sub-section (1), shall, on the expiry of the period`
  line `specified under that sub-section, be eligible for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman shall devote his whole time to the affairs of the Regional Rural Bank and shall`
  line `have, subject to the superintendence, control and direction of the Board, the management of the whole of`
  line `the affairs of the Regional Rural Bank.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(4)`
  line ^5
  line `[The Sponsor Bank] may, at any time, remove the Chairman from office:`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[Provided that no such removal shall be made,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the Chairman is an officer of the Sponsor Bank, except after consultation with the National`
  line `Bank; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, except with the prior approval of the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that] no person shall be removed from his office, under this sub-section, unless he`
  line `has been given an opportunity of showing cause against his removal.]`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairman shall receive such salary and allowances and be governed by such terms and`
  line `conditions of service as may be determined by the ^7`
  line `[the Sponsor Bank in consultation with the National`
  line Bank].
  line
  line `(6) If the Chairman is, by infirmity or otherwise, rendered incapable of carrying out his duties`
  line `or is absent, on leave or otherwise, in circumstances not involving the vacation of office, the`
  line `Central Government may appoint another individual to act as the Chairman during the absence of the`
  line `first-mentioned Chairman`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 8, for "The Central Government" (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line `2. Proviso ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sub-section (1A) (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 73 of 1976, s. 6, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 8, for "The Central Government" (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "the Central Government" (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5076)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title Disqualifications.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5076&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for being appointed or, as the case may be,`
  line `nominated as, and for being, a director, if he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or, at any time has been, adjudged insolvent or has suspended payment of his debt or has`
  line `compounded with his creditors, or`
  line
  line `(b) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court, or`
  line
  line `(c) is, or has been, convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `involves moral turpitude.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5077)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Vacation of the seat of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5077&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a director--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any disqualification specified in section 12, or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent without leave of the Board for more than three consecutive meetings thereof,`
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) A director may resign his office by giving notice thereof in writing to the authority by which he`
  line `was nominated; and, on such resignation being accepted, the director shall be deemed to have vacated his`
  line office.]
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5078)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5078&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of directors of a Regional Rural Bank shall meet at such`
  line `time and place and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its`
  line `meetings as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of the Regional Rural Bank shall preside over every meeting of the Board, and, in`
  line `his absence, such director as the Chairman may generally, or in relation to any particular meeting,`
  line `authorise in this behalf shall preside; and, in the absence of both the Chairman and the director so`
  line `authorised, the directors present at the meeting shall elect one from among themselves to preside over the`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "absence" from a meeting means non-attendance`
  line `for any reason whatsoever at the meeting, or any part of the meeting during which any business is`
  line transacted.
  line
  line `(3) All questions at a meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority of the votes of the directors`
  line `present and voting; and, in case of equality of votes, the person presiding shall have a second or casting`
  line vote.
  line
  line `(4) No director shall, as a director, take part in the discussion of, or vote on, any contract, loan,`
  line `arrangement or proposal entered into or to be entered into, by or on behalf of the Regional Rural Bank, if`
  line `he is, in any way, whether directly or indirectly, interested in the contract, loan, arrangement or proposal`
  line `and, where a director is interested in any such matter, he shall, at the earliest possible opportunity,`
  line `disclose to the Board the nature of his interest in such contract, loan, arrangement or proposal, and where`
  line `he does so, his presence at the meeting shall not count for the purpose of forming any quorum at the time`
  line `of any such discussion or vote, and if he does vote, his vote shall be void:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to such director by reason only of his`
  line being--
  line
  line `(i) a shareholder (other than a director) holding not more than two per cent. of the paid-up capital`
  line `in any public company within the meaning of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or any`
  line `corporation established by or under any law for the time being in force in India or any co-operative`
  line `society, with which the Regional Rural Bank has entered into, or proposes to enter into, any contract,`
  line `loan, arrangement or proposal; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a director of the Regional Rural Bank as such.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5079)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Committees of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5079&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Board may constitute such committees, whether consisting wholly`
  line `of directors or wholly of other persons or partly of directors and partly of other persons, as it may think`
  line `fit, for such purposes as it may decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5080)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Fees and allowances of directors and members of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 10 (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5080&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every director and every`
  line `member of a committee (other than the Chairman) shall be paid such fees and allowances as may be`
  line `determined by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no fees shall be paid to any director, or member of a committee, if he is an officer of the`
  line `Central Government, State Government, the Reserve Bank, ^1`
  line `[National Bank,] Sponsor Bank or any other`
  line bank.
  line
  line `(2) The allowances payable to a director or a member of a committee, who is an officer of the Central`
  line `Government, State Government, Reserve Bank,`
  line ^1
  line `[National Bank,] Sponsor Bank or any other bank, shall`
  line `be paid by the Government or bank by which such officer is employed; and the allowances and fees`
  line `payable to any other director or member of a committee shall be payable by the concerned Regional Rural`
  line Bank.
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (5081)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Staff of Regional Rural Banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5081&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Regional Rural Bank may appoint such number of`
  line `officers and other employees as it may consider necessary or desirable ^1`
  line `[in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed] for the efficient performance of its functions and may determine the terms and conditions of`
  line `their appointment and service:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be lawful for a Sponsor Bank, if requested so to do by a Regional Rural Bank`
  line `sponsored by it, to send, ^2`
  line `*** such number of officers or other employees on deputation to the Regional`
  line `Rural Bank as may be necessary or desirable for the efficient performance of its functions:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the remuneration of officers and other employees appointed by a Regional Rural`
  line `Bank shall be such as may be determined by the Central Government, and, in determining such`
  line `remuneration, the Central Government shall have due regard to the salary structure of the employees of`
  line `the State Government and the local authorities of comparable level and status in the notified area.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, no award, judgment, decree, decision or order of any industrial`
  line `tribunal, court or other authority, made before the commencement of this Act, shall apply to the terms and`
  line `conditions in relation to the persons appointed by a Regional Rural Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) The officers and other employees of a Regional Rural Bank shall exercise such powers and`
  line `perform such duties as may be entrusted or delegated to them by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line
  line `2. The words ", during the first five years of the functioning of a Regional Rural Bank," omitted by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (5082)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Business which a Regional Rural Bank may transact.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5082&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Regional Rural Bank shall`
  line `carry on and transact the business of banking as defined in clause (b) of section 5 of the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), and may engage in one or more forms of business specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), every Regional Rural`
  line `Bank may, in particular, undertake the following types of business, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the granting of loans and advances, particularly to small and marginal farmers and agricultural`
  line `labourers, whether individually or in groups, and to co-operative societies, including agricultural`
  line `marketing societies, agricultural processing societies, co-operative farming societies, primary`
  line `agricultural credit societies or farmers service societies, for agricultural purposes or agricultural`
  line `operations or for other purposes connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(b) the granting of loans and advances, particularly to artisans, small entrepreneurs and persons of`
  line `small means engaged in trade, commerce or industry or other productive activities, within the notified`
  line `area in relation to the Regional Rural Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (5083)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Closure of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5083&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Regional Rural Bank shall cause its books to be closed and`
  line `balanced as on the ^1`
  line `[31st day of March] ^2`
  line `[or such other date in each year as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, specify] and shall appoint with the approval of the Central`
  line `Government auditors for the audit of its accounts:`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[Provided that with a view to facilitating the transition from one period of accounting to another`
  line `period of accounting under this sub-section, the Central Government may, by order published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make such provisions as it considers necessary or expedient for the closing and`
  line `balancing of, or for other matters relating to, the books in respect of the concerned years.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every auditor of a Regional Rural Bank shall be a person who is qualified to act as an auditor of a`
  line `company under section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), and shall receive such remuneration`
  line `as the Regional Rural Bank may fix with the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every auditor shall be supplied with a copy of the annual balance-sheet and profit and loss`
  line `account of the Regional Rural Bank, and a list of all books kept by the Regional Rural Bank, and it shall`
  line `be the duty of the auditor to examine the balance-sheet and vouchers relating thereto, and, in the`
  line `performance of his duties, the auditor--`
  line
  line `(a) shall have, at all reasonable times, access to the books, accounts and other documents of the`
  line `Regional Rural Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) may, at the expense of the Regional Rural Bank, employ accountants or other persons to assist`
  line `him in investigating such accounts; and`
  line
  line `(c) may, in relation to such accounts, examine the Chairman or any officer or employee of the`
  line `Regional Rural Bank.`
  line
  line `(4) Every auditor of a Regional Rural Bank shall make a report to that bank upon the annual`
  line `balance-sheet and accounts and in every such report shall state,--`
  line
  line `(a) whether, in his opinion, the balance-sheet is a full and fair balance-sheet containing all`
  line `necessary particulars and is properly drawn up so as to exhibit a true and fair view of the affairs of the`
  line `Regional Rural Bank, and, in case he had called for any explanation or information, whether it has`
  line `been given and whether it is satisfactory;`
  line
  line `(b) whether or not, the transactions of the Regional Rural Bank, which have come to his notice,`
  line `have been within the powers of that bank;`
  line
  line `(c) whether or not, the returns received from the offices and branches of the Regional Rural Bank`
  line `have been found adequate for the purpose of his audit;`
  line
  line `(d) whether the profit and loss account shows a true balance of profit or loss for the period`
  line `covered by such accounts; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which he considers should be brought to the notice of the Regional Rural`
  line Bank.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2015, s. 7, for "31st day of December" (w.e.f. 4-2-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 33, for "of each year" (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 33, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (5084)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Annual report to be furnished to the shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5084&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] Every Regional Rural Bank shall,`
  line `within ^2`
  line `[three months from the date of the closure of its accounting year, or such further period, not`
  line `exceeding three months, as may be permitted by the Reserve Bank], send to each of its shareholders a`
  line `report as to its working and activities during the accounting year immediately preceding together with a`
  line `copy of its balance-sheet, profit and loss account and the auditor’s report in relation to the accounts of the`
  line `said accounting year.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(2) The Central Government shall cause every auditor’s report and report on the working and`
  line `activities of each Regional Rural Bank to be laid, as soon as may be after they are received, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 20 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 81 of 1985, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-5-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 12, for "sixty days from the date of closure of its accounting year" (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 81 of 1985, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (5085)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Disposal of profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5085&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `After making provisions for bad and doubtful debts, depreciation in assets,`
  line `contributions to staff and superannuation funds and all other matters for which provision is, under law,`
  line `necessary or which are usually provided for by banking companies, a Regional Rural Bank may, out of its`
  line `net profits, declare a dividend.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (5086)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Regional Rural Bank to be deemed to be a co-operative society for purpose of the Income-tax Act, 1961.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5086&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), or any other`
  line `enactment for the time being in force relating to any tax on income, profits or gains, a Regional Rural`
  line `Bank shall be deemed to be a co-operative society.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (5087)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Interest-tax not payable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5087&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Interest-tax`
  line `Act, 1974 (45 of 1974), no Regional Rural Bank shall be liable to pay any tax under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (5088)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 24
  title `Amalgamation of Regional Rural Banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 13 (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5088&sectionno=23A&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[23A. Amalgamation of Regional Rural Banks.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Act, if the Central Government, after consultation with the National Bank, the concerned State`
  line `Government and the Sponsor Bank, is of the opinion that it is necessary in the public interest or in the`
  line `interest of the development of the area served by any Regional Rural Bank or in the interest of the`
  line `Regional Rural Banks themselves, that two or more Regional Rural Banks should be amalgamated, that`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, provide for the amalgamation of such Regional`
  line `Rural Banks (hereafter in this Chapter referred to as the transferor Regional Rural Banks) into a single`
  line `Regional Rural Bank (hereafter in this Chapter referred to as the transferee Regional Rural Bank) with`
  line `such constitution, property, powers, rights, interests, authorities and privileges; and with such liabilities,`
  line `duties and obligations, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall indicate the date with effect from which the`
  line `amalgamation shall become effective.`
  line
  line `(3) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) may also provide for all or any of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the continuance in service of all the employees of the transferor Regional Rural Banks`
  line `(excepting such of them as not being workmen with the meaning of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947`
  line `(14 of 1947) are specifically mentioned in the notification) in the transferee Regional Rural Bank at`
  line `the same remuneration and on the same terms and conditions of service, which they were getting or,`
  line `as the case may be, by which they were being governed, immediately before the date on which the`
  line `amalgamation takes effect;`
  line
  line `(b) notwithstanding anything contained in clause (a), where any of the employees of the`
  line `transferor Regional Rural Banks, not being workmen within the meaning of the Industrial Disputes`
  line `Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) are specifically mentioned in the notification, or where any employee of the`
  line `transferor Regional Rural Banks has by notice in writing given to the transferee Regional Rural Bank`
  line `at any time before the expiry of a period of three months next following the date on which the`
  line `amalgamation takes effect, intimated his intention of not becoming an employee of the transferee`
  line `Regional Rural Bank, the payment to such employee of compensation, if any, to which he is entitled`
  line `under the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947, and such gratuity, provident fund and other retirement`
  line `benefits ordinarily admissible to him under the rules or authorisations of the concerned transferor`
  line `Regional Rural Banks immediately before that date;`
  line
  line `(c) the other terms and conditions for the amalgamation of Regional Rural Banks; and`
  line
  line `(d) the continuance by or against the transferee Regional Rural Bank of any pending legal`
  line `proceeding by or against any transferor Regional Rural Banks and such consequential, incidental and`
  line `supplemental provisions, as may, in the opinion of the Central Government, be necessary to give`
  line `effect to the amalgamation.`
  line
  line `(4) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall, as soon as may be after it has been made, be`
  line `laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_b:
  sectionId (5089)
  sectionNo 23B
  orderNo 25
  title `Notification under section 23A to be sufficient notice to concerned parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 13 (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5089&sectionno=23B&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[23B. Notification under section 23A to be sufficient notice to concerned parties.--(1) A`
  line `notification issued under sub-section (1) of section 23A, shall constitute sufficient notice of the provisions`
  line `thereof to all the parties concerned and shall be binding on the transferor Regional Rural Banks and the`
  line `transferee Regional Rural Bank and to the depositors, creditors, employees and all other persons having`
  line `dealings with such banks.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882) or the`
  line `Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), any notification issued under sub-section (1) of section 23A shall be`
  line `sufficient conveyance, in accordance with the provisions of the notification, of the business, properties,`
  line `assets and liabilities, rights, interests, powers, privileges, benefits and obligations of whatever nature of`
  line `the transferor Regional Rural Banks to the transferee Regional Rural Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) On and from the date on which the amalgamation takes effect under section 23A, any reference to`
  line `the transferor Regional Rural Banks in any agreement, conveyance, assurance, power of attorney or any`
  line `other document of whatsoever nature, shall be deemed to be a reference to the transferee Regional Rural`
  line `Bank and the rights and obligations of the transferor Regional Rural Banks shall be deemed to be the`
  line `rights and obligations of the transferee Regional Rural Bank to the extent specified in the said`
  line amalgamation.]
obj_root_law_sections_23_c:
  sectionId (5090)
  sectionNo 23C
  orderNo 26
  title `Cessation of business of transferor Regional Rural Banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 13 (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5090&sectionno=23C&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[23C. Cessation of business of transferor Regional Rural Banks.--On and from the date on which`
  line `the amalgamation takes effect under section 23A, the transferor Regional Rural Banks shall cease to carry`
  line `on business, including that of making of any payment to any depositors or discharge any liability or`
  line `obligation to the creditors except to the extent as may be necessary for the implementation of the`
  line `provisions of the said amalgamation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_d:
  sectionId (5091)
  sectionNo 23D
  orderNo 27
  title `Liquidation of Regional Rural Banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 13 (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5091&sectionno=23D&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_23_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[23D. Liquidation of Regional Rural Banks.--Where a notification is issued for the amalgamation`
  line `of Regional Rural Banks under sub-section (1) of section 23A, the Central Government may, by a further`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that on such date, as may be specified therein, the transferor`
  line `Regional Rural Banks, which by reason of amalgamation will cease to function, shall stand dissolved and`
  line `such direction shall take effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in section 26.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (5092)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5092&sectionno=24&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Regional Rural Bank shall, in the`
  line `discharge of its functions, be guided by such directions in regard to matters of policy involving public`
  line `interest as the Central Government may, after consultation with the Reserve Bank, give.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any such direction relates to a matter of policy involving`
  line `public interest, the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24_a:
  sectionId (5093)
  sectionNo 24A
  orderNo 29
  title `Inspection, audit and scrutiny by the Sponsor Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 14 (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5093&sectionno=24A&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[24A. Inspection, audit and scrutiny by the Sponsor Bank.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 19 and without prejudice to the provisions of section 35 of the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), the Sponsor Bank shall, from time to time, monitor the progress of the Regional`
  line `Rural Banks sponsored by it and cause inspection, internal audit and scrutiny to be made by one or more`
  line `of its officers and suggest corrective measures to be taken by such Regional Rural Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (5094)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 30
  title `Obligations as to fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 30 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 23-6-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5094&sectionno=25&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Regional Rural Bank shall observe, except as`
  line `otherwise required by law, the practices and usages customary among bankers and, in particular, it shall`
  line `not divulge any information relating to, or to the affairs of, its constituents except in circumstances in`
  line `which it is, in accordance with the law or practice and usage customary among bankers, necessary or`
  line `appropriate for the Regional Rural Bank to divulge.`
  line
  line `(2) Every director, member of a committee or auditor, officer or other employee of a Regional Rural`
  line `Bank shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and secrecy in the form set out`
  line `in the Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to the credit information disclosed under the Credit`
  line `Information Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005 (30 of 2005).]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (5095)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 31
  title `Bar to liquidation of Regional Rural Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5095&sectionno=26&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No provision of law relating to the winding up of`
  line `companies shall apply to a Regional Rural Bank and a Regional Rural Bank shall not be placed in`
  line `liquidation save by order of the Central Government and in such manner as it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (5096)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 32
  title `Defects in appointment or constitution not to invalidate acts or proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5096&sectionno=27&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act of a`
  line `Chairman, acting in good faith, shall be invalid merely by reason of any defect in his appointment or in`
  line `the procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) No act or proceeding of any Board of directors or of any committee of a Regional Rural Bank`
  line `shall be invalid merely on the ground of the existence of any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of,`
  line `such Board or committee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Acts done by a person, acting in good faith, as a director or member of a committee of a Regional`
  line `Rural Bank shall be valid, notwithstanding that it may afterwards be discovered that his appointment was`
  line `invalid by reason of any defect or disqualification or had terminated by virtue of any provision contained`
  line `in any law for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to give validity to any act done by a director or a`
  line `member of any committee of a Regional Rural Bank after his appointment has been shown to the`
  line `Regional Rural Bank to be invalid or to have terminated.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (5097)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 33
  title `Indemnity of directors, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 15 (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5097&sectionno=28&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) A director or a member of a committee of a Regional Rural`
  line `Bank shall not be responsible for any loss or expense caused to such bank by insufficiency or deficiency`
  line `of the value of, or title to, any property or security acquired or taken on behalf of a Regional Rural Bank`
  line `or by the insolvency or wrongful act of any customer or debtor or anything done in, or in relation to, the`
  line `execution of the duties of his office, unless such loss, expense, insufficiency or deficiency was due to any`
  line `wilful act or default on the part of such director or member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of a Regional Rural Bank and every officer of the Central Government or State`
  line `Government or an officer of the Reserve Bank ^1`
  line `[or the National Bank] or the Sponsor Bank and every`
  line `officer or other employee of a Regional Rural Bank shall be indemnified by such bank against all losses`
  line `and expenses incurred by him in, or in relation to, the discharge of his duties except such as have been`
  line `caused by his own wilful act or default.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (5098)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5098&sectionno=29&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after consultation with the ^1`
  line [National
  line `Bank] and the Sponsor Bank, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the additional number of members of the Board may be filled in, under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) the time and place at which the Board of directors of a Regional Rural Bank shall meet and`
  line `the rules of procedure which shall be observed by the Board in regard to the transaction of business at`
  line `its meetings, under sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ba) the manner in which the officers and other employees of the Regional Rural Banks shall be`
  line appointed;]
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for "Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line `2 Ins. by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (5099)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5099&sectionno=30&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] The Board of directors of a Regional Rural Bank may, after`
  line `consultation with the Sponsor Bank and the ^2`
  line `[National Bank], and with the previous sanction of the`
  line `Central Government,`
  line ^3
  line `[by notification in the Official Gazette,] make regulations, not inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, to provide for all matters for which provision is`
  line `necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(2) Every regulation shall, as soon as may be after it is made under this Act by the Board of`
  line `directors, be forwarded to the Central Government and that Government shall cause a copy of the same to`
  line `be laid before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 30 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 1 of 1984, s. 70 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 1988, s. 17, for "Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 28-9-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 34 (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 70 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (5100)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 36
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5100&sectionno=31&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `Central Government may make such order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear`
  line `to it to be necessary for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of five years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (5101)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 37
  title `Act to override the provisions of other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838&sectionId=5101&sectionno=32&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00009_197621_1517807318838
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any`
  line `contract, express or implied, or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act,`
  line `and notwithstanding any custom or usage to the contrary.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
